{"id": "duc04-testb-11:4#12", "contents": "During the Asian crisis, Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad dismissed his Deputy Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim the day after imposing capital controls. Mahathir often won support for his policies by using anti-foreigner rhetoric, especially during times of economic prosperity. In a recent speech, Mahathir attacked foreign currency traders, stating that they are the primary cause of the currency turmoil and have spread it globally, leading to the current recession in many countries."}
